 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uglipthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glip the Gnome</A> at: 7/6/02 5:51:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/02 9:29:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> #1 Character Creation: Race</span><hr size=1> <b>Question:</b>  what Race should I pick?<br>
<b>Answer:</b>  Tough question, in the end game (50+) just about any race is fine.<br>
the only real problem with your race selection is stamina, stamina is important at the end game and its the hardest stat to raise. so pick a race, put starting points into sta to get it to 100 (or as close as you can) then most will put the rest into str as this affects your max bs damage and lets you carry more loot.<br>
<br>
barbarian, the best starting rogue stats<br>
cons? large size, no night vision, has a slight exp penalty.<br>
<br>
dwarfs, the second best rogue starting stats, has night vision, has the styling "roll"<br>
cons? is a small race<br>
<br>
kitty cats, not sure dont have lucin<br>
<br>
halflings, get an exp bonus (slight) night vision <br>
cons? small race normal stats.<br>
<br>
Darkelves, ultravision, small and medium size.<br>
cons? they have the worst starting stats<br>
<br>
all others? have night vision, have normal rogue stats,<br>
woodelves are also small/medium size<br>
<br>
keep in mind that stats are really pretty minor but a sta over 100 keeps you from haveing any bad effects when you run out during a fight. <br>
