<br>
<b>Answer:</b>  The secret hand shake is available to any class/race with "sneak" if you find a vendor who is kos or dubious (or apprehensive even) and you wish to buy or sell with them you need to get behind them and sneak then with a right click you will be able to make your purchases, sell your loot and be gone. even with deep kos vendors. <br>
note. you will become visible when you do this even though hide will not pop up. so after dealing with the vendor you need to rehide before you walk infront of him.<br>
<br>
this is a handy skill to have and well worth mastering, with my Barb rogue I am kos in grob even in de form, but by sneaking into the back of the bank, sqeezing as far between the wall and the guard in the back of the bank as I can, I am able to bank there without troubles.<br>
<br>
oh yeah this also works with quests that dont require talking, the red wine quest is a good example, but you will need to be de/we or smaller to be able to use this trick for that quest as he is burried in the wall and larger races wont be able to get far enough behind him to have sneak faction<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/8/02 2:14:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/5/02 9:34:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> #6 Skills: Staying hidden while... </span><hr size=1> <b>Question:</b>  What can I do while Hiding and Sneaking?<br>
<br>
<b>Answer:</b>  By dropping Hide for only a moment, you can: <br>
- Loot your own corpse in an area with wanderers<br>
- Loot a mob's corpse<br>
- Hand in quest items where another NPC might turn and attack<br>
- Do trade with merchants and bankers <br>
<br>
The reasons you have for this are varied, but the results are the same. Requisites for success are: Hide having been up long enough (10 secs) that you can renew it immediately; Being out of line of sight of any agroing mobs/NPCs.<br>
<br>
Simply, tap the Hotkey matching your Hide button, (hide drops), right-click the corpse/merchant/banker or click to give item to NPC, *quickly* re-Hide. <br>
<br>
Depending on your internet connection, it may be difficult to do trades/sales but looting can be macro'd once the corpse is targetted:<br>
1) /do # (Hide.. to drop it)<br>
2) /loot<br>
3) /do # (Hide.. to rehide)<br>
<br>
Prior to recent patches, it *had* been possible to Hide after starting an effect from a Mask or other item. That has been removed.<br>
A complete page on this subject is at <a href=http://How.to/StayHidden>How.To/StayHidden</a><br>
Mistress Lannella <br>
