<b>Answer:</b>  Dual Wield is an ability which gives you a chance to attack with both your main-hand, and your off-hand. We rogues recive this ability at level 13. All you need to do is put a single point in it, and then put a rogue usable weapon in your offhand slot. When you attack, the skill will raise automatically with use. Your off-hand is completely independant of your main-hand. Also, your off-hand does not receive the damage bonus that your main-hand does, so delay is irrelevent, only ratio matters. Double attack, like dual wield, is an extra attack. We receive this ability at level 17. If you get a successful skill check, you will attack twice with your weapon automatically. When you do get that successful check, you will roll two different numbers for how much damage you do. At around 160 in your double attack ability will also apply to your offhand. <br>
