<br>
<b>Answer:</b>  Below level 51, backstab accounts for roughly 1/3 of a rouge's total damage dealt. Since normal melee attacks account for the bulk of damage dealt, faster weapons will apply the Primary Weapon Damage Bonus more often.<br>
<br>
After 51 and most significantly at 55 and beyond, backstab will account for upwards of 1/2 of damage dealt. At this point a harder hitting main hand becomes of note. Granted, by 55, most rogues will have completed their epic quest. <br>
